Package org.jgum.category.type

Classes in this package model a type categorization as a hierarchical graph of categories.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BottomUpTypeTraversalPolicy<T extends TypeCategory<?>>
    A class facilitating the definition of bottom-up linearization functions in a type categorization.
    ClassCategory<T>
    A category wrapping a class (not an interface).
    InterfaceCategory<T>
    A category wrapping an interface.
    TopDownTypeTraversalPolicy<T extends TypeCategory<?>>
    A class facilitating the definition of top-down linearization functions in a type categorization.
    TypeCategorization  
    TypeCategory<T>
    A category wrapping a class or interface.
    TypeCategoryRoot
    The root category in a categorization of classes and interfaces.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    InterfaceOrder
    Determines the order in which interfaces are going to be visited in a bottom-up type linearization.
    Priority
    Determines if classes should be visited before interfaces or vice versa.
